\\\"### Stats from `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json`\\\", \\\"\\\"]\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:90:- Keep indices up to date and create the versioned metadata directory.\\n./forge/ai_workflows/java_fail_workflow.py:25:from utility_scripts.repo_path_resolver import add_in_metadata_repo_argument, resolve_repo_roots\\n./forge/ai_workflows/java_fail_workflow.py:169:def resolve_repo_paths(explicit_repo_path, explicit_metrics_repo_path, in_metadata_repo: bool = True):\\n./forge/ai_workflows/java_fail_workflow.py:241:    \\\"\\\"\\\"Ensure the metadata directory for the updated library version exists.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n./forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py:13:from utility_scripts.repo_path_resolver import add_in_metadata_repo_argument, resolve_repo_roots\\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/workflow_strategy.py:304:            entry for entry in index_entries if str(entry.get(\\\"metadata-version\\\") or \\\"\\\") == self.version\\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/workflow_strategy.py:343:                f\\\"ERROR: Could not resolve metadata index entry for {self.library} in {index_path_display}.\\\",\\n./forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py:39:from utility_scripts.repo_path_resolver import add_in_metadata_repo_argument, resolve_repo_roots\\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:41:from utility_scripts.repo_path_resolver import add_in_metadata_repo_argument, resolve_repo_roots\\n./forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_fails.py:26:from utility_scripts.repo_path_resolver import add_in_metadata_repo_argument\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:99:* `metadata-version`: Specifies the subdirectory where the GraalVM configuration files (e.g., `reflect-config.json`) reside.\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:100:* `tested-versions`: An array of library versions verified to work with this specific metadata.\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:106:* `default-for`: A Java-format regex used to match library versions if no exact match exists in `tested-versions` (e.g., `\\\"0\\\\\\\\.0\\\\\\\\..*\\\"`).\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:108:* `source-code-url`: URL to the metadata source code location for this index entry. Use `$version$` as the placeholder for this entry's `metadata-version` in versioned URLs.\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:110:* `test-code-url`: URL to the test source code location for this index entry. Use `$version$` as the placeholder for this entry's `metadata-version` in versioned URLs.\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:111:* `documentation-url`: URL to the project documentation for this index entry. Use `$version$` as the placeholder for this entry's `metadata-version` in versioned URLs.\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:122:    \\\"metadata-version\\\": \\\"1.0.0\\\",\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:123:    \\\"tested-versions\\\": [\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:138:     \\\"metadata-version\\\": \\\"1.1.0\\\",\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:144:     \\\"tested-versions\\\": [\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:206:By default, the location of the test code directory mirrors the structure of the metadata directory.\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:26:Application developers consume this repository indirectly: native-build-tools resolves metadata for every dependency in their build and passes it to `native-image`. The user never opts into individual metadata entries. Because of that, the repository's overarching invariant is:\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:43:- A directory tree under `metadata/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/` containing JSON files in the format described by GraalVM's [Native Image Manual Configuration](https://www.graalvm.org/latest/reference-manual/native-image/dynamic-features/Reflection/#manual-configuration) reference.\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:52:- Validation of `index.json` schema and `metadata-version`/`tested-versions` integrity.\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:135:    NBT->>Artifact: resolve packaged metadata bundle\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:137:    NBT->>NBT: for each application dependency,<br/>pick metadata version via index.json<br/>(tested-versions → default-for → latest)\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:138:    NBT->>NI: pass selected metadata directories\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:155:<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:161:**2. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json`** — one per supported artifact, schema [metadata-library-index-schema-v2.0.1.json](../metadata/schemas/metadata-library-index-schema-v2.0.1.json). It is a JSON **array** of entries; each entry's required fields are `metadata-version`, `tested-versions`, and `allowed-packages`, with optional `default-for` (Java regex), `latest: true`, `override: true`, `requires: [\\\"<group>:<artifact>\\\", …]`, `test-version`, `skipped-versions`, `language`, and the four URL fields. Plugin-relevant fields are the first six.\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:163:The schema follows semver, and **minor- and patch-version bumps** (e.g., `v2.0.1` → `v2.0.2` or `v2.0.x` → `v2.1.0`) are guaranteed to be backward-compatible with native-build-tools. Minor bumps add new optional fields used by the website, the test harness, or future tooling (`requires`, `test-version`, `skipped-versions`, `language`, `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, `documentation-url`, `repository-url`); patch bumps refine validation of those same auxiliary fields. The plugin reads only the six fields enumerated above, so an older native-build-tools release continues to resolve metadata correctly against any newer minor or patch version of the schema. Only a **major-version bump** can break the contract, which NFR-4 forbids — schema changes are additive only.\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:165:**3. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/reachability-metadata.json`** — the only file the plugin loads at native-image time. Schema [reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json](../metadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json) (a vendored copy of the upstream GraalVM schema), with top-level keys `reflection`, `jni`, `resources`, `bundles`, `serialization`, and `foreignCalls`. Every entry must carry a `condition.typeReachable` clause (FR-M-2) so the plugin can rely on conditional registration. The legacy split-config layout (`reflect-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, …) is no longer present.\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:169:1. `v ∈ tested-versions` → use that entry's `metadata-version` directory directly.\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:177:    LoadIndex --> Tested{\\\"Any entry with<br/><code>v ∈ tested-versions</code>?\\\"}\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:178:    Tested -- yes --> UseTested[\\\"Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>\\\"]\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:180:    DefaultFor -- yes --> UseDefault[\\\"Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>\\\"]\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:184:    Latest -- yes --> UseLatest[\\\"Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>\\\"]\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:190:    Aux --> Done([\\\"Pass selected metadata<br/>directory to native-image\\\"])\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:206:- **FR-M-6** Exactly one entry in a non-empty `index.json` must carry `latest: true`. If a library version is not in `tested-versions`, the harness selects an entry by matching the optional `default-for` regex.\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:216:- **FR-T-6** Newly added `tested-versions` entries are recorded in `index.json` only after they pass on **every** required environment (enforced by `verify-new-library-version-compatibility`).\\n./docs/CI.md:28:  - Uses: [`generateChangedMetadataTestMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) with base/head SHAs to test only what changed. It batches each changed metadata version's [`tested-versions`](../metadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java-util/index.json) into chunks of up to 30 versions per job, then pulls allowed images, disables Docker networking, validates config, and runs only that batch.\\n./docs/CI.md:31:  - Uses: [`generateChangedTestedVersionsMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) to compute only newly added [`tested-versions`](../metadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java-util/index.json) from the base/head diff and pairs them with the matching [`metadata-version`](../metadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java-util/index.json), then runs [`run-consecutive-tests.sh`](../.github/workflows/scripts/run-consecutive-tests.sh) only for those added versions.\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:166:- `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json`\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:167:- One file per metadata-version directory\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:168:- Each local file contains the `versions` array for that metadata-version only\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:179:- Workflow scripts write execution metrics under `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/execution-metrics.json`.\\n./build.gradle:596:        // Revert metadata directory changes\\n./stats/io.netty/netty-resolver-dns-classes-macos/4.1.74.Final/execution-metrics.json:53:      \\\"metadata_file\\\": \\\"metadata/io.netty/netty-resolver-dns-classes-macos/4.1.74.Final/reachability-metadata.json\\\"\\n./metadata/com.ning/compress-lzf/index.json:4:    \\\"metadata-version\\\" : \\\"1.0.3\\\",\\n./metadata/com.ning/compress-lzf/index.json:10:    \\\"tested-versions\\\" : [\\n./metadata/org.eclipse.jdt.core.compiler/ecj/index.json:4:    \\\"metadata-version\\\" : \\\"4.6.1\\\",\\n./metadata/org.eclipse.jdt.core.compiler/ecj/index.json:11:    \\\"tested-versions\\\" : [\\n./metadata/org.eclipse.jdt.core.compiler/ecj/index.json:19:    \\\"metadata-version\\\" : \\\"4.5\\\",\\n./metadata/org.eclipse.jdt.core.compiler/ecj/index.json:26:    \\\"tested-versions\\\" : [\\n./metadata/org.eclipse.jdt.core.compiler/ecj/index.json:35:    \\\"metadata-version\\\" : \\\"4.4.2\\\",\\n